<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="334" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[831,1437,337,872]" pageId="20" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[831,945,337,360]" pageId="20" pageNumber="334">Remarks:</emphasis>
This specimen is intriguing. The identifi- cation made by Eaton is correct, because it is based on the peculiar arrangement of veins in the cubital and anal fields (
<figureCitation box="[959,1046,433,456]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[831,866,1635,1656]" captionTargetBox="[835,1436,933,1585]" captionTargetId="figure-544@20.[828,1439,932,1585]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 9. Ametropus fragilis Albarda, 1878. (A) Male imago in dorso-lateral view; A1: first anal vein, CuP: posterior cubital vein. Scale bar: 1 mm. (B) Corresponding labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5743814" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5743814/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="334">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
). Eaton (1885) did not mention this specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[1007,1057,465,488]" name="Italy" pageId="20" pageNumber="334">Italy</collectingCountry>
, restricting the distribution of the species to the 
<typeStatus box="[996,1042,497,520]" pageId="20" pageNumber="334">type</typeStatus>
locality in 
<collectingCountry box="[1178,1268,497,520]" name="Netherlands" pageId="20" pageNumber="334">Holland</collectingCountry>
. It is therefore possible that the specimen was identified by Eaton after the publication of his monograph. The first record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Albarda" authorityYear="1878" box="[831,940,593,616]" class="Insecta" family="Ametropodidae" genus="Ametropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<emphasis box="[831,940,593,616]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="334">A. fragilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1010,1059,593,616]" name="Italy" pageId="20" pageNumber="334">Italy</collectingCountry>
was by 
<bibRefCitation author="Turin P. &amp; Bilo M. F. &amp; Belfiore C." box="[1154,1360,593,616]" pageId="20" pageNumber="334" pagination="7 - 14" refId="ref22936" refString="Turin P., Bilo M. F., Belfiore C. 1997. Primo reinvenimento in Italia di Ametropus fragilis Albarda 1878 (Ephemeroptera: Ametropodidae). Lavori della Societa venetiana di Scienza Naturale 22: 7 - 14." type="journal article" year="1997">
Turin 
<emphasis box="[1221,1278,593,616]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="334">et al.</emphasis>
(1997)
</bibRefCitation>
. These authors suspected this surprising discovery to be due to a recent introduction with fishes from Eastern Europe. The fact that this specimen was collected more than 150 years ago indicates that further investigations on the distribution of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1162,1211,753,776]" name="Italy" pageId="20" pageNumber="334">Italy</collectingCountry>
are needed and that its occurrence may be natural. The recent discovery of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Albarda" authorityYear="1878" box="[831,941,817,840]" class="Insecta" family="Ametropodidae" genus="Ametropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<emphasis box="[831,941,817,840]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="334">A. fragilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[980,1059,817,840]" name="Croatia" pageId="20" pageNumber="334">Croatia</collectingCountry>
points in the same direction (
<bibRefCitation author="Cuk R. &amp; Cmrlec K. &amp; Belfiore C." pageId="20" pageNumber="334" pagination="151 - 157" refId="ref19073" refString="Cuk R., Cmrlec K., Belfiore C. 2015. The first record of Ametropus fragilis Albarda, 1878 (Insecta: Ephemeroptera) from Croatia. Natura Croatica 24 (1): 151 - 157." type="journal article" year="2015">
Cuk 
<emphasis box="[831,885,849,872]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="334">et al.</emphasis>
, 2015
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,756,1006,1113]" pageId="20" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis box="[151,292,1006,1027]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="334">
<taxonomicName box="[151,288,1006,1027]" class="Insecta" family="Caenidae" genus="Caenis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lactea">Caenis lactea</taxonomicName>
